House Bill 595 (AS PASSED HOUSE AND SENATE)
By: Representative Greene of the 154th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend an Act providing a homestead exemption from Early County school district ad
2 valorem taxes for educational purposes in the amount of $150,000.00 of the assessed value
3 of the homestead for five years for residents of that school district who are 70 years of age
4 or older, approved May 10, 2021 (Ga. L. 2021, p. 4267), as amended, particularly by an Act
5 approved May 3, 2023 (Ga. L. 2023, p. 4464), so as to remove the sunset date currently on
6 the exemption; to provide for a referendum, effective dates, automatic repeal, mandatory
7 execution of election, and judicial remedies regarding failure to comply; to repeal conflicting
8 laws; and for other purposes.
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
10 SECTION 1.
11 An Act providing a homestead exemption from Early County school district ad valorem taxes
12 for educational purposes in the amount of $150,000.00 of the assessed value of the
13 homestead for five years for residents of that school district who are 70 years of age or older,
14 approved May 10, 2021 (Ga. L. 2021, p. 4267), as amended, particularly by an Act approved
15 May 3, 2023 (Ga. L. 2023, p. 4464), is amended by revising subsection (f) of Section 1 as
16 follows:
